The paper presents a new approach for learning large graphs from data, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of spectral methods suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is concerned with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. The paper also mentions applications such as data clustering and visualization, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of graphs and embeddings suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the mention of scalability and efficiency suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is concerned with the analysis and modeling of large-scale networks.
